The paper presents an approach for mobile robots to learn to navigate in dynamic environments with pedestrians via raw depth inputs, which involves robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also uses depth inputs, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the real-world deployment of the method, which involves systems and control (cs.SY).
